{"word":"γέμω","slug":"γέμω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γέμω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to be full</i>, of a ship, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <i>to be full of</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}